[normal]3. [bold]HS2 and [bold]the [bold]spend on classic rail[bold] [bold]ENHANCEMENTS[bold]Ministers and the DfT attempt to compare HS2 costs with the total ‘investment’
[normal] 
[normal]in the rail network
[normal].  The large majority of the investment in the rail netwo
[normal]rk is routine maintenance and renewals not enhancing the network.  The spend on enhancements for the whole of the network is around £2bn pa while the spend on HS2 would for several years be £4bn or more.  Hence a more accurate statement is that HS2 will ta
[normal]ke 2/3 of the budget available to improve the network!
