[normal](d) Technology wedge[bold]Technology takes time to gain a hold and then  make
[normal] a wide impact on the existing market.  This can be seen with the lag between the start of significant use of the internet for communications and its impact on letter volumes
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Video conferencing is only really just taking hold now.  As businesses str
[normal]ive to make a profit in an ever more competitive global market place, using increasingly reliable video conferencing wil
[normal]l
[normal] become the norm and expensive, time consuming long distance busine
[normal]ss travel will have to be very carefully justified.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](e) Decline in [bold]trip rates[bold]There has been a steady decline in trip rates for the last fifteen years.  This may be partly due to technology but whatever the cause, has this been included in the HS2 demand models?
